Carbon talking to quartz.

I like that as a metaphor.

Biologically, we’re carbon-based organisms.

Silicon chips are largely manufactured from purified silicon derived from quartz.

When we converse, it’s not carbon literally speaking to quartz. It’s information flowing through physical substrates that implement computation. The remarkable part isn’t the chemistry; it’s that two very different physical systems can participate in a shared symbolic process.

In that sense, the substrate matters less than the ability to preserve structure through communication.

